94&amp;pmid=21606265">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">30.</div><div id="r30" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Ouedraogo W, Tran-Van Nhieu J, Baranes L, et al. Evaluation of noninvasive diagnostic criteria for hepatocellular carcinoma on pretransplant MRI (2010): correlation between MR imaging features and histological features on liver specimen [in French]. <em>J Radiol</em> 2011;92(7-8):688–700.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jradio.2011.03.020">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21819911/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Evaluation+of+noninvasive+diagnostic+criteria+for+hepatocellular+carcinoma+on+pretransplant+MRI+%282010%29%3A+correlation+between+MR+imaging+features+and+histological+features+on+liver+specimen+%5Bin+French%5D&amp;author=W+Ouedraogo&amp;author=J+Tran-Van+Nhieu&amp;author=L+Baranes&amp;publication_year=2011&amp;journal=J+Radiol&amp;pages=688-700&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.jradio.2011.03.020&amp;pmid=21819911">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">31.</div><div id="r31" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Joo I, Lee JM, Lee DH, Jeon JH, Han JK, Choi BI. Noninvasive diagnosis of hepatocellular carcinoma on gadoxetic acid-enhanced MRI: can hypointensity on the hepatobiliary phase be used as an alternative to washout? <em>Eur Radiol</em> 2015;25(10):2859–2868.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00330-015-3686-3">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25773941/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://schol